Each time we increase or decrease the value of the x-coordinates by a mul-
tiple of 27, the basic sine curve is repeated. Each portion of the graph in an
interval of 27 is one cycle of the sine function.
The graph of the function y = sin x is its own image under the translation
T27.0. The function y = sin x is called a periodic function with a period of 2T
because for every x in the domain of the sine function, sin x = sin (x + 2π).

Each cycle of the sine curve can be separated into four quarters. In the first
quarter, the sine curve increases from 0 to the maximum value of the function.
In the second quarter, it decreases from the maximum value to 0. In the third
quarter, it decreases from 0 to the minimum value, and in the fourth quarter, it
increases from the minimum value to 0.
